  "prompt": "How do you use Google Account Recovery to reset your password?",
  "response": "If you've forgotten your Google account password or suspect that your account has been compromised, you can use Google Account Recovery to reset your password. Here\u2019s how to do it:\n\n---\n\n### **Steps to Reset Your Password Using Google Account Recovery:**\n\n1. **Go to the Google Account Recovery Page:**\n   - Visit [https://accounts.google.com/signin/recovery](https://accounts.google.com/signin/recovery).\n\n2. **Enter Your Email or Phone Number:**\n   - Input the email address or phone number associated with your Google account.\n   - Click **Next**.\n\n3. **Verify Your Identity:**\n   - Google will ask you to verify your identity using one of the following methods:\n     - **Last Password You Remember:** Enter the last password you recall using for the account.\n     - **Recovery Email or Phone:** If you\u2019ve added a recovery email or phone number, Google will send a verification code to that email or phone.\n     - **Account Creation Date:** Provide the approximate date you created the account.\n     - **2-Step Verification:** If you\u2019ve set up 2-Step Verification, use your backup codes or a trusted device to verify your identity.\n\n4. **Receive the Verification Code (if applicable):**\n   - If Google sends a verification code to your recovery email or phone, enter it in the provided field.\n\n5. **Create a New Password:**\n   - Once your identity is verified, you\u2019ll be prompted to create a new password.\n   - Enter a strong, unique password that you haven\u2019t used before.\n\n6. **Confirm Your New Password:**\n   - Re-enter the new password to confirm it.\n\n7. **Sign In:**\n   - After resetting your password, sign in to your Google account using tsshe new password.\n\n---\n\n### **Tips for a Smooth Recovery Process:**\n- **Add a Recovery Email and Phone Number:** If you haven\u2019t already, add a recovery email and phone number to your Google account. This will make it easier to recover your account in the future.\n- **Keep Your Recovery Information Updated:** Ensure your recovery email and phone number are current.\n- **Use a Password Manager:** Store your passwords securely in a password manager to avoid forgetting them.\n- **Enable 2-Step Verification:** Add an extra layer of security to your account.\n\nIf you encounter issues during the recovery process, you can visit the [Google Account Help Center](https://support.google.com/accounts/) for additional assistance.",
